Since we only need to check if the array is either ascending or descending, we compare the first and last element value and reverse the list. As the result, we only need to do ascending check.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Python
```python
class Solution:
    def isMonotonic(self, A: List[int]) -> bool:
        if A[-1] < A[0]: 
            A = A[::-1]

        for i in range(1, len(A)):
            if A[i] < A[i-1]:
                return False
        return True
```

Java
```java
class Solution {
    public boolean isMonotonic(int[] arr) {
        if (arr[arr.length-1] < arr[0])
            reverse(arr);

        for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] < arr[i-1]) 
                return false;
        }
        return true;
    }

    private void reverse(int[] arr) {
        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length/2; i++) {
            int temp = arr[i];
            arr[i] = arr[arr.length - 1 - i];
            arr[arr.length - 1 - i] = temp;
        }
    }
}
```

