1. Loop through A, only consider those non-equal neighbors (strictly bigger or smaller relations), and count them. 
2. When count >= 2, check if the bigger (smaller) relation changes; if yes, return false; otherwise, continue.
3. return true if no false encounterd.

```
    public boolean isMonotonic(int[] A) {
        boolean smaller = false;
        for (int i = 0, count = 0; i < A.length - 1; ++i) {
            if (A[i] == A[i + 1]) { continue; } // ignore those equal ones.
            if (++count >= 2 && smaller != (A[i] < A[i + 1])) { return false; }
            smaller = (A[i] < A[i + 1]); 
        }
        return true;
    }
``

