# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Traverse back from end point to start point.

A point [x, y] can be reached from 3 previous points: right: [x, y+1], down: [x+1, y] or diagonal: [x+1, y+1].

The number on point[x, y] is fixed, so the previous point with max score forms the path with max score.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Both the max score and count of paths need be recorded. The class `State` is created to record them. The memo array remains to be a 2D array.

Note the diagonal point always has smaller score, it's searched only when right/down points are blocked. Though with memoization this doesn't make much difference since data are cached.

The paths count of current point is same as the count from right/down/diagonal point. Only when right & down points have same max score, the paths count is summed from both. This also means the modulo calculation is only needed when count summed, it would save some time.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(n^2)$$
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(n^2)$$

# Runtime
4ms

# Code
```
class Solution {
    static int MOD = 1_000_000_000 + 7;
    static int[] NUMS = new int[100];
    static {
        for (int i = 0; i < 9; i++) {
            NUMS[i + '1'] = i + 1;
        }
        NUMS['E'] = 0;
    }

    int border;
    byte[][] chars;

    State[][] memo;

    static class State {
        // The max score
        int score = 0;

        // The count of paths to get max score
        int count = 0;

        public State() {}
        public State(int score, int count) {
            this.score = score;
            this.count = count;
        }
    }

    private State search(int row, int column) {
        if (memo[row][column] != null) {
            return memo[row][column];
        }
        if (chars[row][column] == 'X') {
            return memo[row][column] = new State();
        }

        State result = new State();

        if (row < border && column < border) {
            // Search down
            State down = search(row + 1, column);
            // Search right
            State right = search(row, column + 1);

            // When down/right path exists, it always has bigger score than diagonal path
            if (down.count > 0 || right.count > 0) {
                if (down.score > right.score) {
                    result.score = down.score + NUMS[chars[row][column]];
                    result.count = down.count;
                } else if (down.score < right.score) {
                    result.score = right.score + NUMS[chars[row][column]];
                    result.count = right.count;
                } else {
                    result.score = down.score + NUMS[chars[row][column]];
                    result.count = down.count + right.count;
                    // MOD is only needed when count is summed
                    if (result.count > MOD) {
                        result.count %= MOD;
                    }
                }
            } else {
                // Only search diagonal path if down & right path not avaiable
                State diagonal = search(row + 1, column + 1);
                if (diagonal.count > 0) {
                    result.score = diagonal.score + NUMS[chars[row][column]];
                    result.count = diagonal.count;
                }
            }
        } else if (row < border) {
            // At right border, can only search down
            State state = search(row + 1, column);
            if (state.count > 0) {
                result.score = state.score + NUMS[chars[row][column]];
                result.count = state.count;
            }
        } else if (column < border) {
            // At bottom border, can only search right
            State state = search(row, column + 1);
            if (state.count > 0) {
                result.score = state.score + NUMS[chars[row][column]];
                result.count = state.count;
            }
        }

        return memo[row][column] = result;
    }

    public int[] pathsWithMaxScore(List<String> board) {
        int len = board.size();
        border = len - 1;

        // Get board chars
        chars = new byte[len][len];
        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
            chars[i] = board.get(i).getBytes();
        }

        // Create state memo
        memo = new State[len][len];

        // Initially the start point has 0 score, and 1 path count
        memo[border][border] = new State(0, 1);

        // Traverse back from end point [0, 0]
        State result = search(0, 0);

        return new int[]{result.score, result.count};
    }
}
