# Intuition 
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
At very first time i see the problem, it clicks in my mind that i can solve this using maths only, it took me more than a hour and finally i came up with a formula which worked.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
In this solution we're doind addition in parts. I took ```x``` and ```y``` variables as remainder and quotient respectively. Now, we know that we have to add the money from monday to sunday and from every monday it'll increase the money by 1 comparative to the last monday. So, for every complete 7 days of weeks we're doing ```(28*y)```, and for increment of every week, we're doing ```(7*(y*(y-1))/2)``` (by this, we're adding all the increments done).

Now, for the last days which haven't completed the complete week that has to be calculated seperately. So, x is gising us the remainder which means we've to add for that last x number of days which coudn't form a group. so for the series sum, I used ```((x*(x+1))/2)``` and for increment, I added ```(x*y)```, where x gives us the count of numbers in which we've to increment and y gives the weeks that has passed(e.g. in week 3, there has 2 week passed so, we're getting increment of 2 in the next monday, i.e. the 3rd week will be starting from 3, 4, 5.... and so on)

Thanks for the view and comment if you've any doubt.
