**Approach**
You can divide problem into four parts a, b, c, d.
The series is like (commented part is sum) 
1 2 3 ... 7  // 28
2 3 4 ... 8  // 35
3 4 5 ... 9  // 42
You can see I can write series as 28 + 0 + 28 + 7 + 28 + 14 + ... if n%7 == 0
But if n%7 != 0 then I have to add remaining part too
if you look closely you can take 28 and 7 common from all terms and it will become 28*(n/7) and you can take 7 common leading to 7*(0 + 1 + 2 + ...).
We can also do similar when n%7 != 0, by calculating c and d part
```
int totalMoney(int n) {
