solutions.content:
My solution uses the concept of arithmetic progression (AP). First we calculate the total number of complete weeks. For each week start week one, we can tell that an AP is seen starting from 28 (1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 + 6 + 7) going till the total number of complete weeks with a common difference of 7. 

After computing this, we can see that the remaining days also form an AP together. The start number will be number of weeks + 1, and this will go for all the remaining days with a common difference of 1. 

Compute the sum of these two APs and add them. Voila! You have the answer.

```
class Solution {
    public int totalMoney(int n) {
        int weeks = n/7;
        int rem = n%7;
        int start = weeks + 1;
        int sum = rem * (2*start + rem - 1) + 7 * weeks * (2*4 + weeks - 1);
        return sum/2;
    }
}
```

