solution 1: 
the idea is to pre-calculate the 1000 days savings on each day

```
res = [1];
for (let i = 1,week=1,day=1; i < 1000; i++) {
    if (!i%7) {
        week++;
        day = week;
    } else day++;
    res[i] = res[i-1]+day;
}
var totalMoney = function (n,res) {
    return res[n-1];
};
```
solution 2 :

We have nbWeeks= n / 7.

The first week we deposit (1 + 7) * 7 / 2 = 28$.

The wth week we deposit (w + w + 6) * 7 / 2 = (w + 3) * 7 $, the w + 1th week we deposit 7$ more.

So the money we deposit each week is also an arithmetic sequence, whose sum is (28 + 28 + 7 * (nbWeeks - 1)) * nbWeeks / 2 = (49 + 7 * nbWeeks) * nbWeeks / 2.

The last week has d = n % 7 days. We deposit nbWeeks + 1$ on its Monday, so we deposit (nbWeeks + 1 + (nbWeeks + 1 + d - 1)) * d / 2 = (2 * nbWeeks + d + 1) * d / 2 $ for that week.

