# Approach: Math O(1) 100%
The idea of this solution is to get rid of weeks first. Then solve the remaining days.
We see that when solving weeks, we are summing up the sequence of `a, a+7, a+14, ...`.
On the other hand, when solving the days, we are summing up the sequence of `1+s, 2+s, ..., r+s`, which is `r*s + (r+1)*r/2`.
```
class Solution {
    public int totalMoney(int n) {
        // total money
        int res = 0;

        // remaining days after get rid of weeks
        int r = n % 7;

        // streak of 7 days
        int s = (n - r) / 7;

        // increasing sequence: a, a+7, a+14, ...
		// 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 + 6 + 7 = 28
        int a = 28;

		// solve increasing sequence
        res += a*s + 7*s*(s-1)/2;

        // solve remaining days
        if (r > 0) res += r*s + (r+1)*r/2;

        return res;
    }
}
```

