* First check if ```n <= 7```, so as to remove any corner cases and directly return the sum of these ```n``` natural numbers.
* If ```n >= 7```, definitely the final sum will be >= 28. So initialise ```s``` as 28 and iterate thereafter, till ```n != 0```.
* With each iteration, ```n``` reduces by 7, and each element of the list ```l``` gets added by 1. Now, if ```n <= 7```, we should just add the sum of first ```n``` elements of the modified list, else we have to add the sum of all the elements.

Sum of n terms of arithmetic progression = (n*(a+l))/2
where a = first term, l = last term.
Here l = (a + 7 - 1) = a + 6
